      "content": "While dehydration can affect lithium levels and overall health, increasing water intake alone is unlikely to resolve the nausea and shakiness you're experiencing. The best course of action is to discuss any concerns with your doctor, as they can advise you on an appropriate approach and monitor your condition to ensure safe and effective treatment. Cutting back on water abruptly or making significant changes to your fluid intake without professional guidance is not recommended.",
      "source": "target",
